Ten Dead In Bus Crash 
Two buses collided early Monday on a sharp curve near this town about
620 kilometers (385 miles) southeast of Manila, killing 10 people and
injuring 15 others, police reported.
The dead included two children and the wife of one of the drivers,
officials said.
Eight of the dead were passengers on a Philtranco Bus en route to
Manila from Leyte Island. The other bus, operated by Ciudad Bus Lines,
was bound for Samar Island from Manila.
